Torvonnilous<br>
<i>"Never leave for tomorrow what you can do today."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufitemore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fitemore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 3:01:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3903.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for upgrade suggestions</span><hr size=1>   I'd probably suggest that your weapons are your weakest point. Definitely look for an Ornate Sword of the General from the general in Echo. There are plenty of guides around on how to kill him, and a 10/18 1hs with sta and hp is amazing. It also may not be a bad idea to see about camping a Wavecrasher in SG. Also, as your faction seems to be anti-giant, you might want to try to kill the mob that drops both the Frostbringer and Cloak of the Maelstrom. I really don't know how hard he is, but both of those items would be a very nice upgrade for you. <br>
<br>
  It looks like your armor is very decent for ac, but your hp seem kind of low. It'd probably be worth it to try replacing your arms for something with some hp/sta if you can find it, for example. If there are any people you know that have good tradeskills, it may be worth it to round up various items for the PotC earring. You should be able to kill all of the various mobs that you need, and collect items to at least make things cheaper.  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=288863>Fitemore Mystique</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukorwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korwin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/02 3:44:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3903.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> The biggest problem with non-imbued full mithril is that it's ungodly ugly.  It looks like old world steel plate with a light minty tint.<br>
<br>
Personally, I would suggest spending a lot of time in Cazic Thule.  There is a huge selection of hp gear from that zone.  Rubi Shoulders/legs/belt, bloodclaw leggings, mosquito leg earring, iron cog earring (quested, very hard to get).<br>
<br>
And one thing you've got working for you is that you chose the superior warrior race. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubbcookiemonster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BBCookiemonster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/02 6:35:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3903.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for upgrade suggestions</span><hr size=1> When I was tanking ToV from L58-60, I had a Defiance/Frosty combo with the dropped warrior belt from Sky (20's). At times I did indeed have problems with aggro control. I saved up the cash and upgraded my haste to an RBB (31%) and it made a BIG difference in my ability to hold the aggro. If you can't afford, I'd recomment trying a friend's belt if possible to see.<br>
<br>
I now use Wavecrasher/Frosty and do pretty well (altho I don't tank ToV anymore, I dish out C3 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). The Wavecrasher should be able to be camped in SG with a group or 2. Frosty has come down in price considerably.<br>
<br>
Best of luck!<br>
<br>
